        ", Dom Gregory Murray published two booklets, presenting the same views as Vollaerts. In 42 he published Gregorian Rhythm in the Gregorian Centuries; the Literary Evidence which presented excerpts from the medieval theoretical writings in English and Latin. In 42 he published The Authentic Rhythm of Gregorian Chant which statedly presented, in edited fashion,   Delormes and Vollaerts arguments.     This work was followed in 42 by the book Semiologia Gregoriana by Dom Eugène Cardine. In this book, a fairly comprehensive table of the ": null
