        ".     Cardine states that natural speech-rhythms provide a rhythmic basis for the declamation of Gregorian chant. He divides syllabic time into three categories: normal enlarged, more heavy and light, more liquid . Under this interpretation, a one-note syllable would not be considered usually long or longer .     Cardine was employed as a teacher of palaeography and semiology by the ": null
